reviewText: I suppose that is what a comedy act is supposed to be. While he was funny, it was at the expense of others; some of whom were in the audience. Is it worth watching this special - yes. Should you drop everything and rush to watch it - no.
Title: No Offense: Live from New Jersey

reviewText: I have seen Jeffrey Ross on several roasts but never one of his stand ups. He was very good. If you like roasts you like his stand up.
Title: No Offense: Live from New Jersey

reviewText: Wife even watched it with me. There was not a lot of continuous laughter from us, but the few things we liked we still quote from time to time..... "Cookies are a sometimes snack!" YAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!!!!!!!!!

reviewText: I like Jeff Ross but I stopped watching this after about 15 min.  It was ok but not as good as I've seen him and so it was disapointing to me.

reviewText: If you're like me you've seen Jeff Ross on the Comedy Central Roast, and if your reading this you probably really liked him on them, as did I, he is great in them. But in his own stand up special just average.
summary: Great Roaster, Average Stand Up Comic
Title: No Offense: Live from New Jersey

reviewText: To do an hour special successfully you need the follow things: good material, personality and endurance. Ross was ok. His material could of been better structured and his energy lagged a bit. At some point Larry (the audience member) was the best thing on stage. Ross's timing could of been better but Ross has a likable quality to him which is why i figure he got so much applause but not as many laughs.
summary: Maybe straight stand-up isn't his thing.
Title: No Offense: Live from New Jersey
